<body>
    <h1>Computer Hardware and Explanations</h1>
    
    <h2>CPU (Central Processing Unit)</h2>
    <p>The CPU is the "brain" of the computer, responsible for executing instructions and performing calculations.</p>
    
    <h2>GPU (Graphics Processing Unit)</h2>
    <p>The GPU handles graphics rendering and is crucial for tasks like gaming and video editing.</p>
    
    <h2>Memory</h2>
    <p>Memory (RAM) stores data that the CPU is actively using, allowing for quick access and multitasking.</p>
    
    <h2>Storage</h2>
    <p>Storage devices (like SSDs and HDDs) hold your files, applications, and the operating system.</p>
    
    <h2>Motherboard</h2>
    <p>The motherboard connects all hardware components, allowing them to communicate and work together.</p>
    
    <h2>Power Supply</h2>
    <p>The power supply unit provides electricity to all components, ensuring proper functioning.</p>
    
    <h2>Case</h2>
    <p>The computer case houses all components, protecting them and providing cooling through fans and ventilation.</p>
</body>
